  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.1.0 (9de25d1 2022-01-26T14:37:22.300499221+00:00)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge test\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nEven though the number of fuzz runs is configurable in `foundry.toml` and as an environment variable, it is not actually honored.\r\n\r\nTo reproduce:\r\n\r\n- Clone any repository with a fuzz test (for example Rari-Capital/solmate)\r\n- Run `FOUNDRY_FUZZ_RUNS=1 forge test`\r\n- See that the fuzz tests are still run with 256 runs.\r\n\r\nThere is also no `--fuzz-runs` option for `forge test`",
